Currently there is a lack of technical documentation for JIRA Data Center, such as how the index replication works. 
All the official customer-facing docs only describe that it happens automatically, and the Health Checker tool can be used to check its status. Here are two examples:

# https://developer.atlassian.com/display/JIRADEV/Plugin+Guide+to+JIRA+High+Availability+and+Clustering :
{quote}
The Lucene Index is replicated in almost real time and a copy kept local to each instance.
{quote}
# https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/ENTERPRISE/JIRA+Data+Center :
{quote}
(the complete index is replicated on all nodes). This enables instant failover in the event of an outage and index recover in case the index in a node becomes corrupted.
{quote}

It would be helpful for customers to get a better picture of how it works, how often the synchronization is triggered, what situation triggers it etc.

